** '''Player:''' I'm in search of a man named Avan Fitzharmon.
** '''Gem trader:''' Fitzharmon eh? Hmmm.... If I'm not mistaken that's the family name of a member of the Varrockian nobility. You know, I HAVE seen someone of that
** '''Gem trader:''' persuasion around here recently... Wearing a poncey yellow cape he was! Came in here all la-di-dah, high and mighty, asking for jewelry{{sic}} made
** '''Gem trader:''' from 'perfect gold' - whatever that is - like 'normal' golds just not good enough for little lord fancy pants there! I told him to head to the desert
** '''Gem trader:''' 'Cos I know theres gold out there, in them there sand dunes... and if it's not up to his lordships high standards of 'gold perfection'...
** '''Gem trader:''' Maybe we'll all get lucky and the scorpions will deal with him.
** {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Avan===
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|Why are you hanging around a in a scorpion pit?}}
** '''Player:''' Why are you lurking around a scorpion pit?
** '''Man:''' It's a good place to find gold...
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|I'm looking for a man named Avan Fitzharmon}}
** '''Player:''' I'm looking for a man... his name is Avan Fitzharmon.
** '''Man:''' Then you have found him. My name is Avan Fitzharmon.
** '''Player:''' You have a part of your family crest. I am on a quest to retrieve all of the fragmented pieces and restore the crest.
** '''Man:''' Ha! I suppose one of my worthless brothers has sent you on this quest then?
** '''Player:''' No, it was your father who has asked me to do this for him.
** '''Man:''' My... my father wishes this? Then that is a different matter. I will let you have my crest shard, adventurer, but you must first do something for me.
** '''Man:''' There is a certain lady I am trying to impress. As a man of noble birth, I can not give her just any old trinket to show my devotion. What I intend to give her,
** '''Man:''' is a golden ring, embedded with the finest precious red stone available, and a necklace to match this ring. The problem however for me, is that
** '''Man:''' not just any old gold will be suitable. I seek only the purest, the most high quality of gold - what I seek, if you will, is perfect gold.
** '''Man:''' None of the gold around here is even remotely suitable in terms of quality. I have searched far and wide for the perfect gold I desire, but have had no success so
** '''Man:''' in finding it I am afraid. If you can find me my perfect gold, make a ring and necklace from it, and add rubies to them, I will
** '''Man:''' gladly hand over my fragment of the family crest to you.
** '''Player:''' Can you give me any help on finding this 'perfect gold'?
** '''Man:''' I thought I had found a solid lead on its whereabouts when I heard of a dwarf who is an expert on gold who goes by the name of 'Boot'.
** '''Man:''' Unfortunately he has apparently returned to his home, somewhere in the mountains, and I have no idea how to find him.
** '''Player:''' Well, I'll see what I can do.
** {{tact|end}}

