==The Crest Reassembled==
===Talking to Dimintheis===
* '''Player:''' I have retrieved your crest.
* '''Dimintheis:''' Adventurer... I can only thank you for your kindness, although the words are insufficient to express the gratitude I feel!
* '''Dimintheis:''' You are truly a hero in every sense, and perhaps your efforts can begin to patch the wounds that have torn this family apart...
* '''Dimintheis:''' I know not how I can adequately reward you for your efforts... although I do have these mystical gauntlets, a family heirloom that through some power unknown to me, have always returned to the head of the family
* '''Dimintheis:''' whenever lost, or if the owner has died. I will pledge these to you, and if you should lose them return to me, and they will be here.
* '''Dimintheis:''' They can also be granted extra powers. Take them to one of my sons, they should be able to imbue them with a skill for you.
* {{tact|end}}
* {{Qact|Congratulations! Quest complete!}}

==Post Quest dialogue==
===Talking to Caleb after the quest===
* '''Caleb:''' I hear you brought the completed crest to my father. I must say, that was awfully impressive work.
* '''Player:''' I believe your father mentioned you would be able to improve these gauntlets for me...
* '''Caleb:''' Yes, that is correct. I can slightly alter these gauntlets to allow you some of my skill at preparing seafood by making them cooking gauntlets.
* '''Caleb:''' When you wear them you will burn lobsters, sharks and swordfish a lot less. It will be a permanent modification however, so make sure this is what you want.
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|Yes, please do that for me.}}
** '''Player:''' Yes, please do that for me.
** {{tbox|Caleb takes the gauntlets from you, pours some herbs and seasonings on them, bakes them on his range for a short time, then hands them back to you.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|I'll see what your brothers have to offer first.}}
** '''Player:''' I'll see what your brothers have to offer first.
** '''Caleb:''' As you wish. Let me know if you change your mind.
** {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Avan after the quest===
* '''Avan:''' I have received word from my father of your assistance to our family in this matter. You have my thanks for restoring our honour.
* '''Player:''' Your father mentioned that you could improve these gauntlets in some way for me...
* '''Avan:''' Indeed I can. In my long time searching for the 'perfect' gold I learned a lot about gold items. I can improve these gauntlets so that they provide more than normal
* '''Avan:''' experience when smithing gold. I can easily modify these for you.
* {{tselect|Select an option}}
* {{topt|That sounds good, improve them for me.}}
** '''Player:''' That sounds good, improve them for me!
** {{tbox|Avan takes your gauntlets, takes out a small hammer, and pounds them into a slightly new shape, then hands them back to you.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|I think I'll check my other options with your brothers.}}
** '''Player:''' I think I'll check my other options with your brothers before committing myself.
** '''Avan:''' If you feel you really must consort with the likes of them. I await your decision.
** {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Johnathon after the quest===
* '''Johnathon:''' Hello again. My family now considers you a hero.
* '''Player:''' Your father tells me you can improve these gauntlets for me...
* '''Johnathon:''' And right he is at that. Although my skill with Death Rune magiks was not great enough to defeat Chronozon, I am adequately skilled at Chaos Rune magiks.
